### Sprint 2 вЂ” Database Models & API Layer

#### Mongoose Models
| Model | Key Fields |
|-------|-----------|
| `User` | name, email, password (bcrypt), role |
| `HeroConfig` | name, designation, tagline, profileImage, resumeUrl, socialLinks[] |
| `Skill` | name, category, icon, order |
| `Experience` | company, role, startDate, endDate, current, description, technologies[], logo |
| `Project` | title, slug, shortDescription, description, image, githubUrl, liveUrl, category, technologies[], featured, status |
| `Achievement` | title, description, image, date, certificateLink |
| `Certificate` | title, issuer, issueDate, credentialUrl, image |
| `Education` | institute, degree, cgpa, percentage, startYear, endYear, description |
| `Contact` | name, email, subject, message, isRead, createdAt |

#### API Routes (Next.js Route Handlers)
- `POST /api/auth/[...nextauth]` вЂ” NextAuth credentials provider
- `GET|POST /api/skills` вЂ” List / create
- `PUT|DELETE /api/skills/[id]` вЂ” Update / delete
- Same pattern for: projects, experience, achievements, certificates, education, contact
- `POST /api/upload` вЂ” Cloudinary upload (images + PDF)
- `GET|PUT /api/hero` вЂ” Hero section config

